<title>SWEDEN: TABLE-Autoliv posts higher H1 profit.</title>
<headline>TABLE-Autoliv posts higher H1 profit.</headline>
<dateline>STOCKHOLM 1997-07-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Car safety equipment maker Autoliv Inc. posts its results for the six months to June 30, 1997:</p>
<p>					(million USD unless stated)</p>
<p> Profit after fin items		  177.0 vs   160.8</p>
<p> Net sales				 1,683.7 vs 1,636.9</p>
<p> Shr (dollars)				1.01 vs    0.90</p>
<p> Profit after tax			  103.5 vs    92.4</p>
<p> Costs of goods sold		   1,303.8 vs 1,291.4</p>
<p> Sales, admin and other costs	   80.9 vs    71.3</p>
<p> Research and development		 74.2 vs    67.7</p>
<p> Depreciation				 29.5 vs    29.8</p>
<p> Other costs				   0.5 vs     5.4</p>
<p> Operating profit			  194.8 vs   182.1</p>
<p> Associate interests			 4.9 vs     2.0</p>
<p> Tax					    72.6 vs    68.1</p>
<p> Minorities				    0.9 vs     0.3</p>
<p> Write-off for acquired R&amp;D	    732.3 vs     0</p>
<p> Net result after one-off item  LOSS 628.8 vs    92.4 PROFIT</p>
<p>NOTE -- Autoliv Inc. makes car safety equipment such as airbags and seatbelts. Market expectations were for a profit of $169 million before tax, after financial items, for the first six months of the year.</p>
<p>-- Stockholm newsroom +46-8-7001017</p>
